to rest to refresh it...  there are enemys close by...<br><br>so now im a stationary assasin that is no longer have a guild since i kinda killed the the one that gave me quests.<br><br>what should i do..  (yes i was dumb enough to save after the fight) <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29989">My inventory<IMG SRC="http://user.tninet.se/~mhf993y/anna/wanwan2.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usairahlilhealer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sairah Lilhealer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/20/02 1:47:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://sairah.homestead.com/files/sairah.gif height=133 width=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a little thing about disease or whatever it is.</span><hr size=1> could always throw all your stuff on the ground to lose weight.  You have no fear of losing it except if you forget where you dropped it all.<br><br>NPC's won't steal it and it won't decay over time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utreistaania.showPublicProfile?language=EN>treistaania</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/20/02 2:01:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a little thing about disease or whatever it is.</span><hr size=1> tried that but since my str is set to 0 i still cant move. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29989">My inventory<IMG SRC="http://user.tninet.se/~mhf993y/anna/wanwan2.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upontiusont.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pontiusont</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/20/02 4:45:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> That always happens to me and it was so annoying lol.<br>Do you have any divine intervention spells? they port ya to the closest shrine or something and you can pay like 35 gold to get your str back I think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/udekeeverburn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deke Everburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/20/02 5:25:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> yup, blight diseases are permanent. always have blight potions, blight cure spell, or at least a mark spell or some form of gate... I havent been blighted with the str one STILL but have had personality... thats no good when trying to finish a quest =/ <p><HTML><BODY><a Target="_top" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=16042" ><img src="http://www.dragonsong.org/graphics/dekesig.jpg" border=0></a></BODY></HTML></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubiggins.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Biggins</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/20/02 5:25:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Every NPC you ask for "a little advice" tells you to always carry cure disease and cure blight potions.<br><br>I'm not one to listen to advice from the locals. So, I too found myself diseased. I could still move, but <b>no</b> NPC would talk to me. "Cooties Cooties, get away!" I had to run to the nearest shrine (couldn't hitch a boat ride or silt strider). Now I never go without the ability to cure myself. <p><FONT SIZE=+1><a href=http://casusbelli.tamu.edu/magelo.php?mid=13102><B>Biggins Black: Assassin</B></a></FONT><BR><FONT SIZE=-6><FONT COLOR=000000>--stealing your lunch money since 1999--</FONT><BR><FONT SIZE=+1><a href=http://www.casus-belli.net><FONT COLOR=9400D3><b>-Casus Belli; Ayonae Ro-</b></FONT></a><FONT SIZE=-6></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uviscerspineshank.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Viscer Spineshank</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/27/02 6:31:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I'm a bit confused about this.  I have indeed been inflicted with blight in the past....you have a red icon spell effect and the dropping skills that go with it.  Cure blight potions work fine.<br><br>My most recent problem was that I fought some guy that summoned a greater bonewalker (I think thats what it was) and my str was dropped down to 1.  It didn't say I had blight, cure blight and cure common disease potions did not work.  <br><br>Is this some kind of permanent strength drain or something?<br><br>DI is only so good.....the temples have very low stocks of restore str etc potions.<br><br>Any thoughts? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4347"><IMG src="http://www.nwlink.com/~bstevens/Rogues/images/viscer1.jpg" border=0></a><br><a href=http://www.casus-belli.net><I>Casus Belli</I></a>-An Occasion for War<BR>Ayonae Ro<BR>"You can run but you'll just die tired"--KAAOS</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulogixspybreak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Logix Spybreak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>AyRo IRC OP</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/28/02 12:16:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Is this some kind of permanent strength drain or something?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>It's an attribute drain, and it is curable.  You must go to a shrine and select the 'Restore Attribute option.<br><br>Carry Restore STR and other relevant attribute potions on you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uphixer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phixer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/17/02 9:58:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a little thing about disease or whatever it is.</span><hr size=1> ON the subject of Blight and Common diseases as well as attribute drain, I have the following suggestion to anyone who likes it. There's a Wood Elf in Telvanni Tower with a glowing shield (you need to levitate to get up to him, he's above the highest room you can get to without levitating) who fights with a crossbow. He has an amulet on him that, when I got my hands on it, I've never needed another blight potion again (and being a redguard, didn't worry about common diseases anyway). With one use, it restores 1-150 health, cures poisons (I think) common and blight diseases, and restores most lost attributes a bit as well. I've never found anything better, and I'm heavy into exploring (as opposed to quests, I'm only about 4-5 quests into the main storyline). And if you're a member of House Telvanni (as I am) you can get away with it because of their rules (if you take from someone of our house and live, you obviously deserve to keep what you took). A must-have item for anyone who encounters diseases much.<br><br>Also, having a mage with Spellmaking create some restore attribute spells for you (ones with only 1 magicka casting costs) because you can restore attributes while you're diseased, but people still don't like you (because you're still diseased). I keep my stats up and just let the diseases stay until I'm entering town and then cure myself with the amulet (since it cures ALL diseases on you that aren't corprus).<br><br>Haven't found any reusable cures for corprus yet.<br><br>On another side note, the shield isn't bad to use either, I just haven't found anything better yet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usairahlilhealer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sairah Lilhealer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/18/02 3:10:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://sairah.homestead.com/files/sairah.gif height=133 width=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a little thing about disease or whatever it is.</span><hr size=1> I always thought that bodies decayed after a certain amount of time regardless if they have items on them or not. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105067"><img src="http://sairah.homestead.com/files/ElloneSig.jpg" ALT="Click me baby"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uphixer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phixer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/18/02 7:35:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dead bodies... without necromancy.</span><hr size=1> On the subject of bodies, I offer those of you that have been playing a while an example. Go find the Processor from your 'first' quest in Seyda Neen... he should STILL be there, even after you've been playing for days of game time.<br><br>There's also (so far that I've found) a bunch in a temple north of Red Mountain (with a bunch of sixth house people, what am I supposed to do with 11 Sixth house amulets?) two smugglers in a cave north of... aw heck (I'm at work, can't look at the game) the town southwest of Khuul that also has a stilt strider. There's also a dead guar somewhere, I found it by accident once and completely ignored it. Still exploring so I expect there are more.<br><br>Now, a body that YOU create (as in, you kill someone) will disappear eventually... but if they were dead before you get there, it'll stay there... guess decomposition has been halted on them or something... darn necromancers.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=25.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=25.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=25.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.threadControl?topicID=25.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=25.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=25.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub42.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="ayonaerofrm1">General Forum<option value="ayonaerofrm6">NAG (Nearly Anything Goes)<option value="ayonaerofrm7">The Bazaar<option value="ayonaerofrm12">Nuggets<option value="ayonaerofrm14">Guilds<option value="ayonaerofrm8">Raid Forum<option value="ayonaerofrm9">Polls, Tests & Beyond<option value="ayon